The Rivers State University, Port Harcourt, has declared that it has made its environment not to be conducive for cultists and cult-related activities. The Public Relations Officer of the University, Dr. Dike Harcourt- Whyte made the declaration in a chat with LEADERSHIP in Port Harcourt. Harcourt-Whyte stated that the management of the University is working with the Nigerian Police to ensure that cultists do not have space to operate in the institution. He said: “It is almost becoming strange to hear about cultism in this university because we don’t have those kind of activities here anymore. “The university management has taken steps to ensure that such does not happen. We have dedicated lines where people can call in on campus. You can send a text message and I assure you, it will be investigated. “The school management work hand in hand with the Police who go round the school to ensure that such things does not happen. If you come here in the evening, all the street light in the school are working. We make sure that they (cultists) do not have where to survive here.” The University’s image-maker, said the management of the institution is working closely with the Visitor of the University and Rivers State Governor, Nyesom Ezenwo Wike, the make the environment conducive for learning. Harcourt-Whyte said: “Rivers State University is one of the best universities any one would like to be in. We are probably not as old as a lot of universities that people know about, but in the area of teaching and environment, we are one of the best. “From time to time when you come around here, take a peep at the classrooms and see what is happening. The university management, supported by the Visitor, who has the development of the university personal, do everything possible to ensure a conducive learning environment.” 